<div id="outline-container-org786e5de" class="outline-2">
<h2 id="org786e5de"><a href="../../../Notes/sindhu_murthy_annual_review_2026-20260303172449.html#ID-6B119109-F5E5-4133-B9DB-0DADED6718FA">Sindhu Murthy Annual Review 2026</a></h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-org786e5de">
<p>
<b>Student:</b> Sindhu Murthy
<b>Date:</b> Feb 20th 2026
<b>Members present:</b> John Alison / Hy Track / Matteo Cremonesi / Manfred Paulini
<b>Title of current research:</b> Seach for X-&gt;HH-&gt;4b with the CMS detector
</p>

<p>
<b>Summary of Progress Since last review:</b>
Sindhu has prototyped her analysis with data taken in an earlier
running period 2016-2018. She has developed a detailed data-driven
background model for the large QCD multijet background and has
adapted a technique for assessing systematic uncertainties. She has
since turned her attention to data taken in the more recent
data-taking period (2022-2024). This dataset will serve as the
basis for her thesis.
</p>

<p>
In addition to analysis work she has developed a database system that
has proven invaluable to the High-Granularity Calorimeter module
assembly centers. She has been recognized within the collaboration
with an award for this work.
</p>

<p>
<b>Summary of research plan and recommendations of the committee</b>
The committee notes a marked improvement in the presentation of her
research progress and analysis since the last annual review. The
committee recommends that she try to prioritize her thesis analysis
over the database work going forward. We understand there is pressure
to keep up with DB work, but it would be good to start giving priority to
analysis wherever possible.
</p>

<p>
<b>Expected graduation date:</b>  Fall 2027
</p>
